104
00:07:13,163 --> 00:07:15,563
I'm sorry for all this.

105
00:07:15,563 --> 00:07:16,863
No, don't be.

106
00:07:16,863 --> 00:07:19,663
That's right, if you will excuse me,

107
00:07:19,663 --> 00:07:21,663
I'll go check on Yuka.

108
00:07:21,663 --> 00:07:22,963
Please do.

109
00:07:29,963 --> 00:07:31,963
What's with this house anyway?

110
00:07:32,963 --> 00:07:35,763
I'm sorry for all the commotion.

111
00:07:35,763 --> 00:07:36,963
Not at all.

112
00:07:36,963 --> 00:07:39,663
Where's Chiharu?

113
00:07:39,663 --> 00:07:42,063
She went to check on Yuka.

114
00:07:42,063 --> 00:07:43,663
I see.

115
00:07:43,663 --> 00:07:46,863
Is Misuzu sick or something?

116
00:07:49,263 --> 00:07:51,463
She's going to take an afternoon nap.

117
00:07:51,463 --> 00:07:54,063
Afternoon nap?

118
00:07:54,063 --> 00:07:56,463
Yes. She takes an afternoon nap between the hours of 02:00 pm

119
00:07:56,463 --> 00:07:57,563
and 04:00 pm every day.

120
00:07:57,563 --> 00:07:59,163
That's her daily routine.

121
00:07:59,163 --> 00:08:01,563
She goes as far as to drink sleeping pills to do so.

122
00:08:01,563 --> 00:08:04,163
She says she does it to maintain her health and beauty.

123
00:08:23,663 --> 00:08:25,563
Yuka, are you all right?

124
00:08:27,763 --> 00:08:28,963
What happened?

125
00:08:28,963 --> 00:08:30,763
I'm to blame.

126
00:08:30,763 --> 00:08:32,363
I wasn't looking straight.

127
00:08:32,363 --> 00:08:35,363
I'm sorry, I got out of sorts...

128
00:08:35,363 --> 00:08:38,663
Oh, no. You really went all out.

129
00:08:38,663 --> 00:08:40,163
I was watching.

130
00:08:40,163 --> 00:08:42,163
Chiharu staggered in front of the road

131
00:08:42,163 --> 00:08:47,063
and Yuka who tried to avoid her landed in the pond.

132
00:08:47,063 --> 00:08:49,563
It's not Yuka's fault.

133
00:08:49,563 --> 00:08:51,763
You people!

134
00:08:51,763 --> 00:08:54,163
What's all the commotion?

135
00:08:54,163 --> 00:08:55,663
Hey, that car?

136
00:08:55,663 --> 00:08:59,163
Please forgive me, I was careless.

137
00:08:59,163 --> 00:09:01,363
No! I...

138
00:09:01,363 --> 00:09:02,763
Never mind!

139
00:09:02,763 --> 00:09:07,763
Yuka, pack your bags and leave as of today!

140
00:09:07,763 --> 00:09:09,263
I don't believe this.

141
00:09:09,263 --> 00:09:12,563
The first thing you'd ask is if the person's okay or not, right?

142
00:09:12,563 --> 00:09:15,363
The car can be fixed with insurance!

143
00:09:15,363 --> 00:09:17,163
Enough is enough!

144
00:09:17,163 --> 00:09:19,963
Why are you always so selfish like that?

145
00:09:19,963 --> 00:09:23,463
Have you ever thought of the feelings of others at all?

146
00:09:23,463 --> 00:09:26,963
Is that how you should be talking to your parent?

147
00:09:26,963 --> 00:09:30,163
I'm tired. I'm going to rest.

148
00:09:33,663 --> 00:09:35,763
Don't worry, Yuka.

149
00:09:35,763 --> 00:09:38,763
We'll persuade her later.

150
00:09:38,763 --> 00:09:41,063
Then, Mr. Mouri, please help us.

151
00:09:51,563 --> 00:09:54,063
Mr. Mouri, thank you so much.

152
00:09:54,063 --> 00:09:56,663
No, no need to thank me.

153
00:09:56,663 --> 00:09:59,463
All Dad this was press on the gas.

154
00:10:04,263 --> 00:10:06,163
Doesn't it smell like something is burning?

155
00:10:07,563 --> 00:10:10,563
-Madam's room is... -Mother!

156
00:10:10,563 --> 00:10:11,663
Mother!

157
00:10:13,463 --> 00:10:15,063
Misuzu!

158
00:10:22,363 --> 00:10:24,463
-Misuzu! -Mother!

159
00:10:25,463 --> 00:10:27,063
Kyosuke, hold that side.

160
00:10:27,063 --> 00:10:28,163
Yes, sir.

161
00:10:30,063 --> 00:10:31,763
This is?

162
00:10:37,763 --> 00:10:39,363
Today at around 02:00 pm,

163
00:10:39,363 --> 00:10:42,063
there was a fire at the residence of actress Misuzu Shirakawa,

164
00:10:42,063 --> 00:10:45,263
and Mrs. Shirakawa passed away.

165
00:10:45,263 --> 00:10:47,763
"Police Detective Tamagawa" -Mr. Mouri, when you entered the room,

166
00:10:47,763 --> 00:10:49,363
was Mrs. Shirakawa already...

167
00:10:49,363 --> 00:10:50,563
Yes.

168
00:10:50,563 --> 00:10:53,663
It seems that she drank some sleeping pills before taking a nap

169
00:10:53,663 --> 00:10:55,463
so I guess she inhaled a lot of smoke

170
00:10:55,463 --> 00:10:58,463
without being aware of the fire.

171
00:10:58,463 --> 00:10:59,763
I see.

172
00:10:59,763 --> 00:11:03,763
But, the fire seems to have ignited from a strange place.

173
00:11:03,763 --> 00:11:04,963
True.

174
00:11:04,963 --> 00:11:06,763
Did your Mother smoke cigarettes?

175
00:11:06,763 --> 00:11:07,863
No.

176
00:11:07,863 --> 00:11:09,163
Not only Mother,

177
00:11:09,163 --> 00:11:11,963
but no one smokes cigarettes in this house.

178
00:11:14,963 --> 00:11:16,163
This is?

179
00:11:18,463 --> 00:11:19,863
Maybe...

180
00:11:23,163 --> 00:11:25,563
I get the picture.

181
00:11:25,563 --> 00:11:28,363
Which means that this is a homicide.

182
00:11:28,363 --> 00:11:30,363
Moreover, the perp is...

183
00:11:36,063 --> 00:11:38,464
The perp is that person!

184
00:11:40,019 --> 00:11:41,619
So...

185
00:11:41,619 --> 00:11:43,419
It's already sundown

186
00:11:43,419 --> 00:11:46,919
and hard to conclude if this is a homicide or an accident,

187
00:11:46,919 --> 00:11:48,019
so we'll return to the station

188
00:11:48,019 --> 00:11:49,519
and wait for the results from forensics...

189
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:52,019
Please wait, Officer Tamagawa!

190
00:11:53,819 --> 00:11:55,319
Any problem?

191
00:11:55,319 --> 00:11:57,319
Well, no...

192
00:11:58,619 --> 00:12:00,519
Dad?

193
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:01,519
Mr. Mouri?

194
00:12:01,519 --> 00:12:04,419
Don't tell me that this is the Sleeping Kogoro?

195
00:12:04,419 --> 00:12:05,419
What?

196
00:12:05,419 --> 00:12:06,419
Everyone.

197
00:12:06,419 --> 00:12:10,419
The fire was set off deliberately

198
00:12:10,419 --> 00:12:12,419
to kill Mrs Misuzu Shirakawa.

199
00:12:13,419 --> 00:12:16,119
Are you saying that this is a homicide?

200
00:12:16,119 --> 00:12:17,519
Exactly.

201
00:12:17,519 --> 00:12:20,219
Moreover, the perp is here!

202
00:12:22,419 --> 00:12:27,019
But, Dad, back them all of us were near the pond.

203
00:12:27,019 --> 00:12:28,719
Yeah. It's probably a type of fire

204
00:12:28,719 --> 00:12:31,919
caused because of concentrated sunlight to a specific area.

205
00:12:31,919 --> 00:12:33,619
Fire caused by a concentration of sunlight?

206
00:12:33,619 --> 00:12:35,919
Fire caused by a concentration of sunlight is fire

207
00:12:35,919 --> 00:12:38,219
that is set off by things like water from a PET bottle

208
00:12:38,219 --> 00:12:41,619
serving the role of a convex lens.

209
00:12:43,219 --> 00:12:44,819
In other words, Mr. Mouri...

210
00:12:44,819 --> 00:12:47,719
are you saying that the sunlight was concentrated on the surface

211
00:12:47,719 --> 00:12:49,819
of that portrait and was ignited?

212
00:12:49,819 --> 00:12:52,319
But, this room is located on the north side

213
00:12:52,319 --> 00:12:54,719
and sunlight doesn't come in.

214
00:12:54,719 --> 00:12:56,819
Please look out the window.

215
00:12:57,919 --> 00:12:59,219
That glass building which looks

216
00:12:59,219 --> 00:13:02,419
to have been diagonally cut off with a knife.

217
00:13:02,419 --> 00:13:06,119
Doesn't it remind you of something when you look at it, Kyosuke?

218
00:13:08,119 --> 00:13:09,619
That's right.

219
00:13:09,619 --> 00:13:12,419
It's true that when I ran into this room.

220
00:13:14,119 --> 00:13:18,019
But even if the sunlight were to have reflected on that building,

221
00:13:18,019 --> 00:13:21,219
it would only hit the wall on the opposite side...

222
00:13:22,219 --> 00:13:23,519
The mirror.

223
00:13:23,519 --> 00:13:24,719
No.

224
00:13:24,719 --> 00:13:27,419
Even if it reflected off this mirror,

225
00:13:27,419 --> 00:13:31,019
I still think the light wouldn't hit the portrait.

226
00:13:34,019 --> 00:13:36,119
It's true that there seems to be some difficulty here.

227
00:13:36,119 --> 00:13:38,719
Then, let's confirm it.

228
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:41,719
Like this?

229
00:13:41,719 --> 00:13:43,419
A little more upwards.

230
00:13:43,419 --> 00:13:44,719
About here?

231
00:13:44,719 --> 00:13:45,719
Okay.

232
00:13:45,719 --> 00:13:47,719
Please turn on the switch then.

233
00:13:51,819 --> 00:13:53,319
Just as I thought...

234
00:13:53,319 --> 00:13:57,419
The light has gone to the wall opposite the portrait.

235
00:13:57,419 --> 00:14:00,619
Then, Yuka please replace the mirror that is on the floor

236
00:14:00,619 --> 00:14:02,719
to its original position.

237
00:14:02,719 --> 00:14:03,819
Yes, sir.

238
00:14:03,819 --> 00:14:08,219
It probably fell during the commotion of extinguishing the fire.

239
00:14:08,219 --> 00:14:11,519
Can you see the mark on the stand?

240
00:14:13,419 --> 00:14:14,719
Yes, here it is!

241
00:14:14,719 --> 00:14:17,219
There's one on the glass case too,

242
00:14:17,219 --> 00:14:19,919
so can you match it and line it up?

243
00:14:19,919 --> 00:14:20,919
Yes.

244
00:14:24,019 --> 00:14:26,319
Please match the vertical angle too.

245
00:14:26,319 --> 00:14:27,519
Yes, sir.

246
00:14:30,819 --> 00:14:32,119
The light hit the portrait!

247
00:14:32,119 --> 00:14:34,819
Please do the same with the other two too.

248
00:14:43,419 --> 00:14:46,419
In other words, this is what it is.

249
00:14:46,419 --> 00:14:49,219
The light that reflected off the glass building,

250
00:14:49,219 --> 00:14:50,319
went through the window

251
00:14:50,319 --> 00:14:52,419
and reflected on the full length mirror.

252
00:14:52,419 --> 00:14:54,619
On top of that it also reflected

253
00:14:54,619 --> 00:14:56,819
on the three mirrors on top of the glass case.

254
00:14:56,819 --> 00:15:00,019
Then, it concentrated on one point of the portrait.

255
00:15:00,019 --> 00:15:03,219
The perp probably set the position of the mirrors

256
00:15:03,219 --> 00:15:05,619
meticulously in place beforehand.

257
00:15:05,619 --> 00:15:08,219
But, please try remembering.

258
00:15:08,219 --> 00:15:10,719
When I was shown here before noon

259
00:15:10,719 --> 00:15:13,919
I mistakenly knocked over the mirror.

260
00:15:13,919 --> 00:15:17,319
Which means that it was highly likely that the position of the mirror

261
00:15:17,319 --> 00:15:19,819
may have been displaced from where the perp had placed it.

262
00:15:19,819 --> 00:15:22,719
Despite this, the fire burst out just as

263
00:15:22,719 --> 00:15:25,119
the perp had planned.

264
00:15:25,119 --> 00:15:27,219
Which means...

265
00:15:27,219 --> 00:15:30,519
The perp returned the position of the mirrors in the right place?

266
00:15:30,519 --> 00:15:35,019
Yes. Moreover, there's only one person who could've done it.

267
00:15:35,019 --> 00:15:38,319
The person who remained back in this room

268
00:15:38,319 --> 00:15:40,419
when all of us went out to the terrace,

269
00:15:40,419 --> 00:15:42,219
Ms. Chiharu Shirakawa!

270
00:15:43,919 --> 00:15:46,119
You're the only one!

