323
00:18:24,919 --> 00:18:28,919
It's probably because I touched the lily accidently at some point, no?

324
00:18:28,919 --> 00:18:31,919
-Just because of that you can't... -Accidentally at what point?

325
00:18:31,919 --> 00:18:34,219
I don't remember!

326
00:18:34,219 --> 00:18:36,419
Please carefully try to remember.

327
00:18:36,419 --> 00:18:41,619
The lily was decorated in the vase on top of the glass case.

328
00:18:41,619 --> 00:18:45,119
If the pollen got attached to your right sleeve,

329
00:18:45,119 --> 00:18:48,819
it means that you reached over your right hand,

330
00:18:48,819 --> 00:18:52,419
to the left of the lily, and did something.

331
00:18:52,419 --> 00:18:54,819
Then what was there?

332
00:18:56,319 --> 00:18:57,519
Right.

333
00:18:57,519 --> 00:19:01,719
Over there was what was used in the experiment a while ago

334
00:19:01,719 --> 00:19:06,119
to reflect and concentrate light, the mirrors!

335
00:19:10,619 --> 00:19:11,819
Chiharu.

336
00:19:11,819 --> 00:19:15,719
Chiharu, why? Why did you kill...

337
00:19:15,719 --> 00:19:17,019
Miss Chiharu.

338
00:19:18,319 --> 00:19:21,619
That woman, she kept calling me "Miss Chiharu"

339
00:19:21,619 --> 00:19:23,619
